Sentencas: The novel composite electrolytes were obtained by mixing LSGM (La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O2.85) powders which were synthesized by acrylamide polymerization with binary carbonates.
Titulo: Thermal Stability of LSGM-Carbonates Composite Electrolytes for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Ageing, cycling and longtime fuel cell performance tests were used to evaluate the stability of LSGM-(Li/Na)(2)CO3 composite materials.
Titulo: Thermal Stability of LSGM-Carbonates Composite Electrolytes for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The result shows that the sample has a relatively stable conductivity of 0.07 similar to 0.09 S.cm(-1) during 650 h measurement at 600 degrees C in air.
Titulo: Thermal Stability of LSGM-Carbonates Composite Electrolytes for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The composites keep stable weight during thermal cycling below 700 degrees C, and demonstrate a good stability after 5 thermal cycles.
Titulo: Thermal Stability of LSGM-Carbonates Composite Electrolytes for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The cell based on LSGM-20%(Li/Na)(2)CO3 composite electrolyte delivers an average output of 285 mW.cm(-2) in 960 min operation corresponding to the constant current density 0.79 A.cm(-2).
Titulo: Thermal Stability of LSGM-Carbonates Composite Electrolytes for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
